from tqdm import tqdm

def get_quantity_canceled(data):
    """      .
    
           ,   
           .
            ,
       NaN.

    Args:
        data (DataFrame):   

    Returns:
        Series:     
    """
    #   Series   ,    .
    quantity_canceled = pd.Series(np.zeros(data.shape[0]), index=data.index)    
    negative_quantity = data[(data['Quantity'] < 0)].copy()
    #   
    with tqdm(total=negative_quantity.shape[0], desc ="Total", ncols = 80) as tqdm_bar:
        
        for index, col in negative_quantity.iterrows():
            #  DataFrame   
            df_test = data[(data['CustomerID'] == col['CustomerID']) &
                           (data['StockCode']  == col['StockCode']) &
                           (data['InvoiceDateTime'] < col['InvoiceDateTime']) &
                           (data['Quantity'] > 0)].copy()
            # -       
            if (df_test.shape[0] == 0):
                #    
                quantity_canceled.loc[index] = np.nan
            # -    
            #      QuantityCanceled
            elif (df_test.shape[0] == 1):
                index_order = df_test.index[0]
                quantity_canceled.loc[index_order] = -col['Quantity']      
            # -   
            #       QuantityCanceled     ,
            #         -
            elif (df_test.shape[0] > 1):
                df_test.sort_index(axis=0 ,ascending=False, inplace = True)        
                for ind, val in df_test.iterrows():
                    if val['Quantity'] < -col['Quantity']:
                        continue
                    quantity_canceled.loc[ind] = -col['Quantity']
                    break

            tqdm_bar.update()    
    
    return quantity_canceled

def frame_figure(fig, file_name, height="800", width="100%"):
    """        Plotly
        fig:  Figure
        file_name:   html 
        width, height: ,    
    """
    fig.write_html(file_name)
    return IFrame(src=file_name, width=width, height=height)
In[41]:
#
def rfm_boxes(rfm_table):
    """  boxplot  RFM 
    """
    boxes = [px.box(rfm_table, x=column) for column in rfm_table.columns]
    fig = make_subplots(
        rows=1, cols=3, 
        subplot_titles=("Recency","Frequency", "Monetary")
    )
    for i, box in enumerate(boxes):
        fig.add_trace(boxes[i]['data'][0], row=1, col=i+1)
    fig.update_layout(showlegend=True)
    return fig

In[70]:
def plot_cluster_profile(grouped_data, n_clusters):
    """        .

    Args:
        grouped_data (DataFrame): ,     
                                     .
        n_clusters (int):  
        
        Return: go.Figure()
    """
    #   ,     0-1.
    scaler = MinMaxScaler()
    grouped_data = pd.DataFrame(scaler.fit_transform(grouped_data), columns=grouped_data.columns)
    #   
    features = grouped_data.columns
    #   
    fig = go.Figure()
    #        
    for i in range(n_clusters):
        #         
        fig.add_trace(go.Scatterpolar(
            r=grouped_data.iloc[i].values, # 
            theta=features, #  
            fill='toself', #   
            name=f'Cluster {i}', #    
        ))
    #   
    fig.update_layout(
        showlegend=True, #  
        autosize=False, #    
        #width=800, #  ( )
        height=780, #  ( )
    )
    #  
    return fig
